problems.problem:
Given sets $A, B$, and $C$, express each of the following sets in terms of $A, B$, and $C$, using the symbol $ \cup ,  \cap ,$ and $-$. 
    \begin{align*}
        D & = \{ x : x \in A \text{ and } (x \in B \text{ or } x \in C ) \}, \\
        E & = \{ x : (x \in A \text{ and } x \in B) \text{ or } x \in C \}, \\
        F & = \{ x : x\in A \text{ and } (x \in B \implies x \in C) \}.
    \end{align*}
